BEE-LFS - bee for linux from scratch
  by Marius Tolzmann <marius@mariux.de> 2011
  by Tobias Dreyer <dreyer@molgen.mpg.de> 2011

This [0] is a repository of bee-files to create a linux from scratch (LFS).

The bee-files are based on the LFS BOOK (development version) [1].

They can be build using bee [2].

All files in this repository are distributed in the hope that it will
be useful, but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied
warranty of MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

[0] https://github.com/mariux/bee-lfs
[1] http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/view/development/
[2] https://github.com/mariux/bee
